EMERGENCY LANDING PROGRAM
Some of the flying test using our available rockets have
not finished successfully, so our engineers decided to
prepare some emergency landing protocols to avoid risks
in the following trials. The proposed designs for the
landing zone are the following:
In previous designs, dark zones represent the secure
landing spaces. Our engineers want to order the previous
designs in ascending probability of the rocket landing on
a safe zone. The password to open the doors is obtained
by ordering the previous designs in ascending probability
of a save landing. For example, if the probability of
landing safely in design A is 3/4, for design B is 2/4,
and for design C is 1/4, since 3/4 > 2/4 > 1/4, the
password would be ABC.
Furthermore, we know the following additional
information:
1. Points marked as O are the centers of the figures.
2. External polygons are regular.
3. In design B, the marked points are the centers of
the sides.
4. The probability to land in every point of the figure
is constant.
Which is the doors password?
